00:26:55.890 --> 00:26:59.000
on another question, which is
more about the Affordable Care

00:26:59.000 --> 00:26:59.500
Act.

00:26:59.500 --> 00:27:01.958
DAMON TWEEDY: So I will talk
but the other part too though.

00:27:03.904 --> 00:27:05.320
AUDIENCE: The
Affordable Care Act,

00:27:05.320 --> 00:27:07.390
obviously we have some
huge problems with it

00:27:07.390 --> 00:27:10.820
like the fact that so many
states did not expand Medicaid.

00:27:10.820 --> 00:27:11.820
Huge problem.

00:27:11.820 --> 00:27:13.620
But two things that
it's definitely done,

00:27:13.620 --> 00:27:16.510
one is it's insured a
heck of a lot more people.

00:27:16.510 --> 00:27:20.250
And number two is it has
made preventive care free.

00:27:20.250 --> 00:27:22.810
Although it did not
make the drugs free,

00:27:22.810 --> 00:27:24.700
and that's a really
huge issue I'm

00:27:24.700 --> 00:27:28.224
sure for issues like
hypertension, for example.

00:27:28.224 --> 00:27:30.960
But here's my question about it.

00:27:30.960 --> 00:27:34.100
With all these newly
insured people,

00:27:34.100 --> 00:27:37.430
you would think that the
demand for primary care

00:27:37.430 --> 00:27:38.710
is now growing.

00:27:38.710 --> 00:27:41.050
It's gotta be
bigger than it ever

00:27:41.050 --> 00:27:43.490
was before the demand for it.

00:27:43.490 --> 00:27:48.100
Nonetheless, I've read
recently that like too many

00:27:48.100 --> 00:27:52.120
of the poor insured patients are
